    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-01-13T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-01-13T22:00:00-05:00" n="286"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d286">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">702.9493/55: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase—Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-01-14T11:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 14, 1928—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 14—11:05 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>28.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>7. It is my continued hope that events may shape themselves in such a way that I
                    may find it expedient in the near future (sometime in February would be
                    suitable) to go to Shanghai, at which time every effort will be made by me to
                    effect a satisfactory settlement of the Nanking outrages. …</p>
                <p>8. Copy sent to Tokio by mail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
